  "root_text": {
    "snp2.7:0.1": "Sutta Nipāta 2.7 ",
    "snp2.7:0.2": "Brāhmaṇadhammikasutta ",
    "snp2.7:1.1": "Evaṁ me sutaṁ—",
    "snp2.7:1.2": "ekaṁ samayaṁ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṁ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. ",
    "snp2.7:1.3": "Atha kho sambahulā kosalakā brāhmaṇamahāsālā jiṇṇā vuḍḍhā mahallakā addhagatā vayoanuppattā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṁsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṁ sammodiṁsu. ",
    "snp2.7:1.4": "Sammodanīyaṁ kathaṁ sāraṇīyaṁ vītisāretvā ekamantaṁ nisīdiṁsu. Ekamantaṁ nisinnā kho te brāhmaṇamahāsālā bhagavantaṁ etadavocuṁ: ",
    "snp2.7:1.5": "“sandissanti nu kho, bho gotama, etarahi brāhmaṇā porāṇānaṁ brāhmaṇānaṁ brāhmaṇadhamme”ti? ",
    "snp2.7:1.6": "“Na kho, brāhmaṇā, sandissanti etarahi brāhmaṇā porāṇānaṁ brāhmaṇānaṁ brāhmaṇadhamme”ti. ",
    "snp2.7:1.7": "“Sādhu no bhavaṁ gotamo porāṇānaṁ brāhmaṇānaṁ brāhmaṇadhammaṁ bhāsatu, sace bhoto gotamassa agarū”ti. ",
    "snp2.7:1.8": "“Tena hi, brāhmaṇā, suṇātha, sādhukaṁ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti. ",
    "snp2.7:1.9": "“Evaṁ, bho”ti kho te brāhmaṇamahāsālā bhagavato paccassosuṁ. ",
    "snp2.7:1.10": "Bhagavā etadavoca: ",
    "snp2.7:2.1": "“Isayo pubbakā āsuṁ, ",
    "snp2.7:2.2": "saññatattā tapassino; ",
    "snp2.7:2.3": "Pañca kāmaguṇe hitvā, ",
    "snp2.7:2.4": "attadatthamacārisuṁ. ",
    "snp2.7:3.1": "Na pasū brāhmaṇānāsuṁ, ",
    "snp2.7:3.2": "na hiraññaṁ na dhāniyaṁ; ",
    "snp2.7:3.3": "Sajjhāyadhanadhaññāsuṁ, ",
    "snp2.7:3.4": "brahmaṁ nidhimapālayuṁ. ",
    "snp2.7:4.1": "Yaṁ nesaṁ pakataṁ āsi, ",
    "snp2.7:4.2": "dvārabhattaṁ upaṭṭhitaṁ; ",
    "snp2.7:4.3": "Saddhāpakatamesānaṁ, ",
    "snp2.7:4.4": "dātave tadamaññisuṁ. ",
    "snp2.7:5.1": "Nānārattehi vatthehi, ",
    "snp2.7:5.2": "sayanehāvasathehi ca; ",
    "snp2.7:5.3": "Phītā janapadā raṭṭhā, ",
    "snp2.7:5.4": "te namassiṁsu brāhmaṇe. ",
    "snp2.7:6.1": "Avajjhā brāhmaṇā āsuṁ, ",
    "snp2.7:6.2": "ajeyyā dhammarakkhitā; ",
    "snp2.7:6.3": "Na ne koci nivāresi, ",
    "snp2.7:6.4": "kuladvāresu sabbaso. ",
    "snp2.7:7.1": "Aṭṭhacattālīsaṁ vassāni, ",
    "snp2.7:7.2": "(komāra) Brahmacariyaṁ cariṁsu te; ",
    "snp2.7:7.3": "Vijjācaraṇapariyeṭṭhiṁ, ",
    "snp2.7:7.4": "Acaruṁ brāhmaṇā pure. ",
    "snp2.7:8.1": "Na brāhmaṇā aññamagamuṁ, ",
    "snp2.7:8.2": "napi bhariyaṁ kiṇiṁsu te; ",
    "snp2.7:8.3": "Sampiyeneva saṁvāsaṁ, ",
    "snp2.7:8.4": "saṅgantvā samarocayuṁ. ",
    "snp2.7:9.1": "Aññatra tamhā samayā, ",
    "snp2.7:9.2": "utuveramaṇiṁ pati; ",
    "snp2.7:9.3": "Antarā methunaṁ dhammaṁ, ",
    "snp2.7:9.4": "nāssu gacchanti brāhmaṇā. ",
    "snp2.7:10.1": "Brahmacariyañca sīlañca, ",
    "snp2.7:10.2": "ajjavaṁ maddavaṁ tapaṁ; ",
    "snp2.7:10.3": "Soraccaṁ avihiṁsañca, ",
    "snp2.7:10.4": "khantiñcāpi avaṇṇayuṁ. ",
    "snp2.7:11.1": "Yo nesaṁ paramo āsi, ",
    "snp2.7:11.2": "Brahmā daḷhaparakkamo; ",
    "snp2.7:11.3": "Sa vāpi methunaṁ dhammaṁ, ",
    "snp2.7:11.4": "Supinantepi nāgamā. ",
    "snp2.7:12.1": "Tassa vattamanusikkhantā, ",
    "snp2.7:12.2": "Idheke viññujātikā; ",
    "snp2.7:12.3": "Brahmacariyañca sīlañca, ",
    "snp2.7:12.4": "Khantiñcāpi avaṇṇayuṁ. ",
    "snp2.7:13.1": "Taṇḍulaṁ sayanaṁ vatthaṁ, ",
    "snp2.7:13.2": "Sappitelañca yāciya; ",
    "snp2.7:13.3": "Dhammena samodhānetvā, ",
    "snp2.7:13.4": "Tato yaññamakappayuṁ. ",
    "snp2.7:14.1": "Upaṭṭhitasmiṁ yaññasmiṁ, ",
    "snp2.7:14.2": "Nāssu gāvo haniṁsu te; ",
    "snp2.7:14.3": "Yathā mātā pitā bhātā, ",
    "snp2.7:14.4": "Aññe vāpi ca ñātakā; ",
    "snp2.7:14.5": "Gāvo no paramā mittā, ",
    "snp2.7:14.6": "Yāsu jāyanti osadhā. ",
    "snp2.7:15.1": "Annadā baladā cetā, ",
    "snp2.7:15.2": "Vaṇṇadā sukhadā tathā; ",
    "snp2.7:15.3": "Etamatthavasaṁ ñatvā, ",
    "snp2.7:15.4": "Nāssu gāvo haniṁsu te. ",
    "snp2.7:16.1": "Sukhumālā mahākāyā, ",
    "snp2.7:16.2": "Vaṇṇavanto yasassino; ",
    "snp2.7:16.3": "Brāhmaṇā sehi dhammehi, ",
    "snp2.7:16.4": "Kiccākiccesu ussukā; ",
    "snp2.7:16.5": "Yāva loke avattiṁsu, ",
    "snp2.7:16.6": "Sukhamedhitthayaṁ pajā. ",
    "snp2.7:17.1": "Tesaṁ āsi vipallāso, ",
    "snp2.7:17.2": "Disvāna aṇuto aṇuṁ; ",
    "snp2.7:17.3": "Rājino ca viyākāraṁ, ",
    "snp2.7:17.4": "Nāriyo samalaṅkatā. ",
    "snp2.7:18.1": "Rathe cājaññasaṁyutte, ",
    "snp2.7:18.2": "Sukate cittasibbane; ",
    "snp2.7:18.3": "Nivesane nivese ca, ",
    "snp2.7:18.4": "Vibhatte bhāgaso mite. ",
    "snp2.7:19.1": "Gomaṇḍalaparibyūḷhaṁ, ",
    "snp2.7:19.2": "Nārīvaragaṇāyutaṁ; ",
    "snp2.7:19.3": "Uḷāraṁ mānusaṁ bhogaṁ, ",
    "snp2.7:19.4": "Abhijjhāyiṁsu brāhmaṇā. ",
    "snp2.7:20.1": "Te tattha mante ganthetvā, ",
    "snp2.7:20.2": "Okkākaṁ tadupāgamuṁ; ",
    "snp2.7:20.3": "Pahūtadhanadhaññosi, ",
    "snp2.7:20.4": "Yajassu bahu te vittaṁ; ",
    "snp2.7:20.5": "Yajassu bahu te dhanaṁ. ",
    "snp2.7:21.1": "Tato ca rājā saññatto, ",
    "snp2.7:21.2": "Brāhmaṇehi rathesabho; ",
    "snp2.7:21.3": "Assamedhaṁ purisamedhaṁ, ",
    "snp2.7:21.4": "Sammāpāsaṁ vājapeyyaṁ niraggaḷaṁ; ",
    "snp2.7:21.5": "Ete yāge yajitvāna, ",
    "snp2.7:21.6": "Brāhmaṇānamadā dhanaṁ. ",
    "snp2.7:22.1": "Gāvo sayanañca vatthañca, ",
    "snp2.7:22.2": "Nāriyo samalaṅkatā; ",
    "snp2.7:22.3": "Rathe cājaññasaṁyutte, ",
    "snp2.7:22.4": "Sukate cittasibbane. ",
    "snp2.7:23.1": "Nivesanāni rammāni, ",
    "snp2.7:23.2": "Suvibhattāni bhāgaso; ",
    "snp2.7:23.3": "Nānādhaññassa pūretvā, ",
    "snp2.7:23.4": "Brāhmaṇānamadā dhanaṁ. ",
    "snp2.7:24.1": "Te ca tattha dhanaṁ laddhā, ",
    "snp2.7:24.2": "Sannidhiṁ samarocayuṁ; ",
    "snp2.7:24.3": "Tesaṁ icchāvatiṇṇānaṁ, ",
    "snp2.7:24.4": "Bhiyyo taṇhā pavaḍḍhatha; ",
    "snp2.7:24.5": "Te tattha mante ganthetvā, ",
    "snp2.7:24.6": "Okkākaṁ puna mupāgamuṁ. ",
    "snp2.7:25.1": "Yathā āpo ca pathavī ca, ",
    "snp2.7:25.2": "Hiraññaṁ dhanadhāniyaṁ; ",
    "snp2.7:25.3": "Evaṁ gāvo manussānaṁ, ",
    "snp2.7:25.4": "Parikkhāro so hi pāṇinaṁ; ",
    "snp2.7:25.5": "Yajassu bahu te vittaṁ, ",
    "snp2.7:25.6": "Yajassu bahu te dhanaṁ. ",
    "snp2.7:26.1": "Tato ca rājā saññatto, ",
    "snp2.7:26.2": "Brāhmaṇehi rathesabho; ",
    "snp2.7:26.3": "Nekā satasahassiyo, ",
    "snp2.7:26.4": "Gāvo yaññe aghātayi. ",
    "snp2.7:27.1": "Na pādā na visāṇena, ",
    "snp2.7:27.2": "Nāssu hiṁsanti kenaci; ",
    "snp2.7:27.3": "Gāvo eḷakasamānā, ",
    "snp2.7:27.4": "Soratā kumbhadūhanā; ",
    "snp2.7:27.5": "Tā visāṇe gahetvāna, ",
    "snp2.7:27.6": "Rājā satthena ghātayi. ",
    "snp2.7:28.1": "Tato devā pitaro ca, ",
    "snp2.7:28.2": "Indo asurarakkhasā; ",
    "snp2.7:28.3": "Adhammo iti pakkanduṁ, ",
    "snp2.7:28.4": "Yaṁ satthaṁ nipatī gave. ",
    "snp2.7:29.1": "Tayo rogā pure āsuṁ, ",
    "snp2.7:29.2": "Icchā anasanaṁ jarā; ",
    "snp2.7:29.3": "Pasūnañca samārambhā, ",
    "snp2.7:29.4": "Aṭṭhānavutimāgamuṁ. ",
    "snp2.7:30.1": "Eso adhammo daṇḍānaṁ, ",
    "snp2.7:30.2": "Okkanto purāṇo ahu; ",
    "snp2.7:30.3": "Adūsikāyo haññanti, ",
    "snp2.7:30.4": "Dhammā dhaṁsanti yājakā. ",
    "snp2.7:31.1": "Evameso aṇudhammo, ",
    "snp2.7:31.2": "Porāṇo viññugarahito; ",
    "snp2.7:31.3": "Yattha edisakaṁ passati, ",
    "snp2.7:31.4": "Yājakaṁ garahatī jano. ",
    "snp2.7:32.1": "Evaṁ dhamme viyāpanne, ",
    "snp2.7:32.2": "Vibhinnā suddavessikā; ",
    "snp2.7:32.3": "Puthū vibhinnā khattiyā, ",
    "snp2.7:32.4": "Patiṁ bhariyāvamaññatha. ",
    "snp2.7:33.1": "Khattiyā brahmabandhū ca, ",
    "snp2.7:33.2": "Ye caññe gottarakkhitā; ",
    "snp2.7:33.3": "Jātivādaṁ nirākatvā, ",
    "snp2.7:33.4": "Kāmānaṁ vasamanvagun”ti. ",
    "snp2.7:34.1": "Evaṁ vutte, te brāhmaṇamahāsālā bhagavantaṁ etadavocuṁ: ",
    "snp2.7:34.2": "“abhikkantaṁ, bho gotama …pe… ",
    "snp2.7:34.3": "upāsake no bhavaṁ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupete saraṇaṁ gate”ti. ",
    "snp2.7:34.4": "Brāhmaṇadhammikasuttaṁ sattamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "snp2.7:0.1": "Anthology of Discourses 2.7 ",
    "snp2.7:0.2": "Brahmanical Traditions ",
    "snp2.7:1.1": "So I have heard. ",
    "snp2.7:1.2": "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. ",
    "snp2.7:1.3": "Then several old and well-to-do brahmins of Kosala—elderly and senior, who were advanced in years and had reached the final stage of life—went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him. ",
    "snp2.7:1.4": "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, they sat down to one side and said to the Buddha: ",
    "snp2.7:1.5": "“Worthy Gotama, are the ancient traditions of the brahmins exhibited these days among brahmins?” ",
    "snp2.7:1.6": "“No, brahmins, they are not.” ",
    "snp2.7:1.7": "“If you wouldn’t mind, worthy Gotama, please teach us the ancient traditions of the brahmins.” ",
    "snp2.7:1.8": "“Well then, brahmins, listen and apply your mind well, I will speak.” ",
    "snp2.7:1.9": "“Yes, worthy sir,” they replied. ",
    "snp2.7:1.10": "The Buddha said this: ",
    "snp2.7:2.1": "“The ancient seers used to be ",
    "snp2.7:2.2": "restrained and austere. ",
    "snp2.7:2.3": "Having given up the five sensual titillations, ",
    "snp2.7:2.4": "they lived for their own true good. ",
    "snp2.7:3.1": "Brahmins used to own no cattle, ",
    "snp2.7:3.2": "nor gold coin or grain. ",
    "snp2.7:3.3": "Chanting was their money and grain, ",
    "snp2.7:3.4": "which they guarded as a gift from god. ",
    "snp2.7:4.1": "Food was prepared for them ",
    "snp2.7:4.2": "and left beside their doors. ",
    "snp2.7:4.3": "People believed that food prepared in faith ",
    "snp2.7:4.4": "should be given to them. ",
    "snp2.7:5.1": "With colorful clothes, ",
    "snp2.7:5.2": "lodgings and houses, ",
    "snp2.7:5.3": "prosperous nations and countries ",
    "snp2.7:5.4": "honored those brahmins. ",
    "snp2.7:6.1": "Brahmins used to be inviolable and ",
    "snp2.7:6.2": "invincible, protected by principle. ",
    "snp2.7:6.3": "No-one ever turned them away ",
    "snp2.7:6.4": "from the doors of families. ",
    "snp2.7:7.1": "For forty-eight years ",
    "snp2.7:7.2": "they led the spiritual life. ",
    "snp2.7:7.3": "The brahmins of old pursued ",
    "snp2.7:7.4": "their quest for knowledge and conduct. ",
    "snp2.7:8.1": "Brahmins never transgressed with another, ",
    "snp2.7:8.2": "nor did they purchase a wife. ",
    "snp2.7:8.3": "They lived together in love, ",
    "snp2.7:8.4": "joining together by mutual consent. ",
    "snp2.7:9.1": "Brahmins never approached their wives for sex ",
    "snp2.7:9.2": "during the time outside ",
    "snp2.7:9.3": "the fertile phase of the menstrual cycle ",
    "snp2.7:9.4": "after menstruation. ",
    "snp2.7:10.1": "They praised chastity and morality, ",
    "snp2.7:10.2": "integrity, tenderness, and fervor, ",
    "snp2.7:10.3": "gentleness and harmlessness, ",
    "snp2.7:10.4": "and also patience. ",
    "snp2.7:11.1": "He who was supreme among them, ",
    "snp2.7:11.2": "godlike, staunchly vigorous, ",
    "snp2.7:11.3": "did not engage in sex ",
    "snp2.7:11.4": "even in a dream. ",
    "snp2.7:12.1": "Training in line with their duties, ",
    "snp2.7:12.2": "many smart people here ",
    "snp2.7:12.3": "praised chastity and morality, ",
    "snp2.7:12.4": "and also patience. ",
    "snp2.7:13.1": "They begged for rice, ",
    "snp2.7:13.2": "bedding, clothes, ghee, and oil. ",
    "snp2.7:13.3": "Having collected them legitimately, ",
    "snp2.7:13.4": "they arranged a sacrifice. ",
    "snp2.7:14.1": "But they slew no cows ",
    "snp2.7:14.2": "while serving at the sacrifice. ",
    "snp2.7:14.3": "Like a mother, father, or brother, ",
    "snp2.7:14.4": "or some other relative, ",
    "snp2.7:14.5": "cows are our best friends, ",
    "snp2.7:14.6": "the fonts of medicine. ",
    "snp2.7:15.1": "They give food and strength, ",
    "snp2.7:15.2": "and beauty and happiness. ",
    "snp2.7:15.3": "Knowing these benefits, ",
    "snp2.7:15.4": "they slew no cows. ",
    "snp2.7:16.1": "The brahmins were delicate and tall, ",
    "snp2.7:16.2": "beautiful and glorious. ",
    "snp2.7:16.3": "They were keen on all the duties ",
    "snp2.7:16.4": "required by their own traditions. ",
    "snp2.7:16.5": "So long as they continued in the world, ",
    "snp2.7:16.6": "people flourished happily. ",
    "snp2.7:17.1": "But perversion crept into them ",
    "snp2.7:17.2": "little by little when they saw ",
    "snp2.7:17.3": "the transformation of the king ",
    "snp2.7:17.4": "and the ladies in all their finery. ",
    "snp2.7:18.1": "Their chariots were harnessed with thoroughbreds, ",
    "snp2.7:18.2": "well-made with bright canopies, ",
    "snp2.7:18.3": "and their homes and houses ",
    "snp2.7:18.4": "were neatly divided section by section. ",
    "snp2.7:19.1": "They were lavished with herds of cattle, ",
    "snp2.7:19.2": "and furnished with bevies of lovely ladies. ",
    "snp2.7:19.3": "This extravagant human wealth ",
    "snp2.7:19.4": "was coveted by the brahmins. ",
    "snp2.7:20.1": "They compiled hymns to that end, ",
    "snp2.7:20.2": "approached King Okkāka and said, ",
    "snp2.7:20.3": "‘You have plenty of money and grain. ",
    "snp2.7:20.4": "Sacrifice! For you have much treasure. ",
    "snp2.7:20.5": "Sacrifice! For you have much money.’ ",
    "snp2.7:21.1": "Persuaded by the brahmins, ",
    "snp2.7:21.2": "the king, chief of charioteers, performed ",
    "snp2.7:21.3": "horse sacrifice, human sacrifice, ",
    "snp2.7:21.4": "the sacrifices of the ‘casting of the yoke-pin’, <j>the ‘royal soma drinking’, and the ‘unimpeded’. ",
    "snp2.7:21.5": "When he had carried out these sacrifices, ",
    "snp2.7:21.6": "he gave riches to the brahmins. ",
    "snp2.7:22.1": "There were cattle, bedding, and clothes, ",
    "snp2.7:22.2": "and ladies in all their finery; ",
    "snp2.7:22.3": "chariots harnessed with thoroughbreds, ",
    "snp2.7:22.4": "well-made with bright canopies; ",
    "snp2.7:23.1": "and lovely homes, ",
    "snp2.7:23.2": "nicely divided section by section. ",
    "snp2.7:23.3": "Having furnished them with different grains, ",
    "snp2.7:23.4": "he gave riches to the brahmins. ",
    "snp2.7:24.1": "When they got hold of that wealth, ",
    "snp2.7:24.2": "they arranged to store it up. ",
    "snp2.7:24.3": "Falling under the sway of desire, ",
    "snp2.7:24.4": "their craving grew and grew. ",
    "snp2.7:24.5": "They compiled hymns to that end, ",
    "snp2.7:24.6": "approached King Okkāka once more and said, ",
    "snp2.7:25.1": "‘Like water and earth, ",
    "snp2.7:25.2": "gold coin, riches, and grain, ",
    "snp2.7:25.3": "are cows for humankind, ",
    "snp2.7:25.4": "as they are essential for creatures. ",
    "snp2.7:25.5": "Sacrifice! For you have much treasure. ",
    "snp2.7:25.6": "Sacrifice! For you have much money.’ ",
    "snp2.7:26.1": "Persuaded by the brahmins, ",
    "snp2.7:26.2": "the king, chief of charioteers, ",
    "snp2.7:26.3": "had many hundred thousand cows ",
    "snp2.7:26.4": "slain at the sacrifice. ",
    "snp2.7:27.1": "Neither with feet nor with horns ",
    "snp2.7:27.2": "do cows harm anyone at all. ",
    "snp2.7:27.3": "Cows meek as lambs, ",
    "snp2.7:27.4": "supply buckets of milk. ",
    "snp2.7:27.5": "But taking them by the horns, ",
    "snp2.7:27.6": "the king slew them with a sword. ",
    "snp2.7:28.1": "At that the gods and the ancestors, ",
    "snp2.7:28.2": "with Indra, the titans and monsters, ",
    "snp2.7:28.3": "roared out: ‘This is a crime against nature!’ ",
    "snp2.7:28.4": "as the sword fell on the cows. ",
    "snp2.7:29.1": "There used to be three kinds of illness: ",
    "snp2.7:29.2": "greed, starvation, and old age. ",
    "snp2.7:29.3": "But due to the slaughter of cows, ",
    "snp2.7:29.4": "this grew to be ninety-eight. ",
    "snp2.7:30.1": "This crime of the rods ",
    "snp2.7:30.2": "is of ancient descent. ",
    "snp2.7:30.3": "Killing innocent creatures, ",
    "snp2.7:30.4": "the sacrificers forsake righteousness. ",
    "snp2.7:31.1": "And that is how this mean old practice ",
    "snp2.7:31.2": "was criticized by sensible people. ",
    "snp2.7:31.3": "Wherever they see such a thing, ",
    "snp2.7:31.4": "folk criticize the sacrificer. ",
    "snp2.7:32.1": "With righteousness gone, ",
    "snp2.7:32.2": "peasants and menials were split, ",
    "snp2.7:32.3": "as were many aristocrats, ",
    "snp2.7:32.4": "and wives looked down on their husbands. ",
    "snp2.7:33.1": "Aristocrats and brahmins only by kin, ",
    "snp2.7:33.2": "and others protected by their clan, ",
    "snp2.7:33.3": "neglecting their genealogy, ",
    "snp2.7:33.4": "fell under the sway of sensual pleasures.” ",
    "snp2.7:34.1": "When he had spoken, those well-to-do brahmins said to the Buddha, ",
    "snp2.7:34.2": "“Excellent, worthy Gotama! Excellent! … ",
    "snp2.7:34.3": "From this day forth, may the worthy Gotama remember us as lay followers who have gone for refuge for life.” "
  },
